  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\nAn option for Rook to integrate the object gateway management capability in the Ceph dashboard.\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\nThe Ceph Dashboard is a great visual tool for managing Ceph.  A strong use case for Ceph is as an object store for things like registry etc, and as such it's useful to have management capabilities over the object store function using the Ceph Dashboard.  Currently this is possible through some manual configuration but not using Rook.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\nThe below commands were successful using a Rook 0.9 deployment in Openshift 3.10\r\n\r\n**Commands to Enable Dashboard Support for Object Store**:\r\nLogin to the rgw pod after enabling the object store using Rook and create a new object user with the system flag:\r\n```\r\nradosgw-admin user create --uid=dashboard --display-name=dashboard --system\r\n```\r\n\r\nExecute the following against the toolbox pod (with ceph preconfigured etc for management):\r\n```\r\noc exec rook-ceph-tools-5cb84cb5b4-np7dx ceph dashboard set-rgw-api-host rook-ceph-rgw-my-store\r\noc exec rook-ceph-tools-5cb84cb5b4-np7dx ceph dashboard set-rgw-api-port 8080\r\noc exec rook-ceph-tools-5cb84cb5b4-np7dx ceph dashboard set-rgw-api-access-key <access-key>\r\noc exec rook-ceph-tools-5cb84cb5b4-np7dx ceph dashboard set-rgw-api-secret-key <secret-key>\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce dashboard has been configured as per above, the object store functionality can be managed from the dashboard.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/19749398/53422755-0efc0180-39ae-11e9-88b8-c53e990c5c90.png)\r\n",
